<p><i><b>Stand on Zanzibar</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Dystopia" title="Dystopia">dystopic</a> <a href="/wiki/New_Wave_(science_fiction)" title="New Wave (science fiction)">New Wave</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novel</a> written by <a href="/wiki/John_Brunner_(novelist)" title="John Brunner (novelist)">John Brunner</a> and first published in 1968 (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0099191105" class="internal">ISBN 0-09-919110-5</a>). The book won a <a href="/wiki/Hugo_Award_for_Best_Novel" title="Hugo Award for Best Novel">Hugo Award for Best Novel</a> at the 27th <a href="/wiki/World_Science_Fiction_Convention" title="World Science Fiction Convention" class="mw-redirect">World Science Fiction Convention</a> in 1969.</p>
